<P>
   RATPACK _ HBO airs ``The Rat Pack,'' a film where none of the
stars really look like Sinatra or Dino or Sammy _ but it grows on
you anyway. It scores big. (Jubera, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   TV-SURFER _ The first, and some say the best, new series (though
that's debatable) of the fall season _ airs Sunday. It's ``That
'70s Show'' on Fox _ and full of jokes about disco, Vienna
sausages, smoking dope, bell bottoms and Todd Rundgren. It's
definitely not a sitcom for everybody _ but aging baby boomers will
likely get a kick out of it. Also debuting Sunday _ ``Holding The
Baby.'' In a few quick words: it's particularly awful; short quotes
from Chris Rock about return of his HBO comedy series. (Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
