<P>
   MURRAY-COLUMN _ ST. PETERSBURG, Russia _ Czar Nicholas II and
his family were murdered by Bolsheviks in the cellar of a farmhouse
in 1918. In later years the house itself was demolished by a local
communist chief, by the name of Yeltsin, for fear the site might
become a shrine. The status of Nicholas II has since been elevated,
not to mention that of Yeltsin. (Murray, Cox News Service) MOVED
WEDNESDAY.
