gossiping, and yet being a defender of propriety?''
</P>
<P>
   Typo cheers, ``I think you've got it, Boss! Let me type those
parameters into our MacRighteousness program here ... lessee,
self-righteous tongue clucking is a Four on the nonverbal axis,
minding one's own business is a Nine ....! Let's rush the printout
up to Hyperba's office, Boss!''
</P>
<P>
   &UR; PANEL FIVE &LR; : (closeup of a three-column Page 1 logo): Absentee
Publisher Gimlet Peen smiles out at the readers under a horsecollar
bearing the legend DUMB CLUCK.
