<P>
   SCI-1918-FLU (Spitsbergen, Norway) _ Six young coal miners,
buried in permafrost since falling victim to the Spanish flu of
1918, are being carefully exhumed this week. Scientists plan to
take ``core samples'' from the bodies, in hope of building a
genetic profile of the mysterious virus that killed 20 million to
40 million people before vanishing. By John Noble Wilford.
