second-biggest takeover in the American insurance industry and the
latest big transaction in the consolidating financial services
sector. The agreement launches AIG, best known for its global
commercial property-casualty lines and life-insurance products,
squarely into the arena of financial services for individual
investors. By Joseph B. Treaster.
</P>
<P>
   FED-REPORT (Washington) _ The Federal Reserve releases minutes
of the July meeting of its policy committee. By Sylvia Nasar.
</P>
<P>
   NOVELL-EARNINGS (Undated) _ Novell posts earnings. By Lawrence
M. Fisher.
</P>
<P>
   MICROSOFT-ANTITRUST (Washington) _ The start of the Microsoft
antitrust trial is delayed until Sept. 23. By Joel Brinkley.
</P>
<P>
   HONDA-EARNINGS (Tokyo) _ Honda is benefiting more than ever from
its global reach, which once earned it ridicule in Japan. The
company today said that net income rose 26 percent in the latest
quarter as strong sales in the United States and the weak yen
compensated for sinking car sales in Japan. By Stephanie Strom.
</P>
<P>
   MARKETPLACE (Undated) _ The daily Marketplace column.
</P>
<P>
   MARKET (New York) _ Stock market developments: The Dow Jones
Industrial Average was down 32 points at 1:40 p.m.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; COMMENTARY &LR;  (``k'' code)
</P>
<P>
   Russell Baker's ``Observer''; details to come.
</P>
