<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-SPICE-NOTARO-AZR </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
SPICE WORLD COULD USE REALITY CHECK FROM AN OLD PRO 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 By LAURI NOTARO  
 c.1998 The Arizona Republic  
<TEXT>
<P>
   PHOENIX - I'll tell ya what I want, what I really, really want.
</P>
<P>
   I wanna be a Spice Girl.
</P>
<P>
   I hear there's an opening, and that the Pre-Fab Four need a
replacement for Ginger Spice, who left the group earlier this year
because Scary Spice was picking on her.
</P>
<P>
   I think I could do it. I've been onstage before. When I was 9,
my dance school put on a recital for an old-folks home and, right
smack in the middle of our tap-dancing salute to the theme song
from ``The Sting,'' an old man pushed his wheelchair to the front
row, unzipped his fly and relieved himself all over the floor. At
that age, I was completely unaware that men could even do that. As
I stared at the puddle in front of me, my little feet kept
shuffling off to ``Buffalo'' as Judy Garland's voice shouted in my
head _ ``Go ON with the show! Go ON with the show!'' _ while the
rest of my dance class burst into tears, walked offstage or just
plain sat down.
</P>
<P>
   Now that's a pro. I've taken the Official Spice Girls quiz and
found, not by coincidence, I believe, that the one I have most in
common with is that spunky Ginger. We share the bad habits:
``picking our eye boogies''; only telling our friends if there is a
secret sale at our favorite store; and constantly interrupting
others.
</P>
<P>
   I'm a shoo-in.
</P>
<P>
   I already know what my Spice Girl focus is going to be.
Considering that I already had boobs and acne by the time the rest
of the Spice Girls were about to be born, I'll be known as Old
Spice. I'll set the other Spicies straight by informing them that
``girl power'' never meant anything more than their perky cup size,
and that they should quit acting as the voice of feminism until
their boobs have dropped, they've purchased a power tool and have
started growing hairs out of their chins.
</P>
<P>
   Old Spice is about reality. The Old Spice doll will come with a
pack of cigarettes, a chair (Old Spice sits down a lot), tweezers,
a pimple on her neck and inner thighs that rub together and make a
rash. If you pull the string in her back, she won't cry out, ``This
Spice is HOT!'' or ``Be free!'' but ``Pass the salt,'' ``Shut up,
I'm watching TV,'' and ``Does this mole look weird to you?''
</P>
<P>
   If you're frightened by the vision of Old Spice in spandex
shorts and a halter top, I can reassure you that it would take
three days of consecutive shaving for me to be able to wear
something like that. I'm thinking that Old Spice should probably
wear a pea coat, knickers and, on special occasions (like visiting
hospitals, the Grammys and meeting the Queen), an eye patch and a
hook hand in compliance with the nautical theme.
</P>
<P>
   Old Spice, in keeping with her focus, will act as an advocate
for back fat, the swags of underarm flesh that jiggle when mature
women wave and the glory of elastic waistbands. She'll reassure the
prepubescent audience that girl power means it's OK to pick at your
face, body hair should be completely ignored, and Twinkies are
indeed a meal in themselves.
</P>
<P>
   I'm not too worried about Scary Spice picking on me, either,
because with one demonstration of how easily a hook hand can rip
out a belly ring, I think all issues will become completely
resolved.
</P>
<P>
   Old Spice should also become the boss of writing lyrics, and
I've already come up with new ones:
</P>
<P>
   ``If you wanna be my lover''
</P>
<P>
   ``I won't hang with a jerk''
</P>
<P>
   ``Buy your own beer and smokes''
</P>
<P>
   ``Get outta bed and go to word''
</P>
<P>
   ``If you wanna be my lover''
</P>
<P>
   ``I understand you're beguiled''
</P>
<P>
   ``But quit looking in my windows''
</P>
<P>
   ``A restraining order has been filed''
</P>
<P>
   ``If you wanna be my lover''
</P>
<P>
   ``No, you can't move in''
</P>
<P>
   ``Living in your car may be hot''
</P>
<P>
   ``But premarital sex is a sin!''
</P>
<P>
   Honestly, I realize that it's only a matter of time before the
Spice phenomenon goes the way of Menudo and New Kids on the Block
and the girls go back to working for Heidi Fleiss, so I've got to
act fast. But before the window closes, Old Spice is determined to
get her peg leg through it, even if it does involve capitalizing on
Ginger Spice's bad career move.
</P>
<P>
   I can't be that concerned about it. Ginger Spice is doing fine
in her solo career, because I'm pretty sure I saw her last Saturday
night strutting in a crosswalk in downtown Phoenix, selling her
girl power for 15 bucks a pop.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
Laurie Notaro is a freelance writer. Write to her in care of the
``Rep,`` P.O. Box 2245 NF-19, Phoenix, AZ 85002. &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
