<TEXT>
<P>
   The New York Times News Service calls your attention to the
following travel features and columns moved during the last week.
</P>
<P>
   For retransmissions of these stories, please call 888-346-9867.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; PLACES AND DESTINATIONS &LR;
</P>
<P>
   TRAVEL-LONGBEACH-BOS (Long Beach, Calif.) _ This oceanside city
has tried repeatedly over the last few decades to become a tourist
mecca, but with limited success. By Adam Pertman.
</P>
<P>
   TRAVEL-WOLF-BOS (Gardiner, Mont.) _ A few miles south of town,
down in the park, the wolves are thriving on a diet of extremely
rare elk chops. By M.R. Montgomery.
</P>
<P>
   TRAVEL-COLUMN-BOS (Undated) _ The Earth is yours to behold in
Maine. By Jerry Morris.
</P>
<P>
   TRAVEL-NOTES-BOS (Undated) _ When you visit a famous building
like Salem's House of the Seven Gables, which has been around since
1668, you get a hefty serving of history with your tour. By Richard
Carpenter.
</P>
