<HEADLINE>
&HT;    
 &HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Filmmaking in the south
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   By the numbers, how Georgia's filmmaking industry stacks up
against neighboring states (all numbers refer to 1997, except where
noted):
</P>
<P>
   -- Georgia: Total number of productions (movies and TV): 13.
</P>
<P>
   Estimated dollar impact on state: $247.57 million.
</P>
<P>
   Total budget of state film office: $368,566.
</P>
<P>
   -- North Carolina: Total number of productions (movies, TV,
commercials): 41.
</P>
<P>
   Estimated dollar impact on state: $329 million.
</P>
<P>
   Total budget of state film office: $523,000.
</P>
<P>
   -- South Carolina:
</P>
<P>
   Total number of productions (movies, TV): 6.
</P>
<P>
   Estimated dollar impact on state: $20.2 million.
</P>
<P>
   Total budget of state film office: $422,697 (Note: Total fiscal
year 1998-99 appropriation for state film, entertainment and sports
development office).
</P>
<P>
   Source: State film offices
</P>
