<P>
   PROFILE-BISHOP-BOS (Boston) _ BARBARA HARRIS: THE ECLECTIC
ECCLESIASTIC &QL; 
Bishop Barbara Clementine Harris knelt at the altar, her
68-year-old knees padded only by her cassock's thin beige cloth.
Head lowered, she gently lifted a wet cloth from a plastic tub and
washed a man's bare feet. The foot washing is a yearly Episcopal
ritual, symbolic of Jesus' washing the Apostles' feet, a show of
humility. For those gathered, seeing Harris humbled was impressive.
After all, she is the suffragan (assisting) bishop for
Massachusetts, which means she is second in command of the nation's
largest Episcopal diocese. By Alisa Valdes-Rodriguez. Photo.
</P>
