   MORMON-MISSIONARIES-ART-BOS (Boston) _ Tenille Roberts and
Amanda Williams are privates in a formidable army. Their uniform is
a pressed white shirt, ankle-length skirt, and sensible walking
shoes. Their weapon is a Spanish version of The Book of Mormon.
``We're here because the Lord wants us here,'' said Williams,
riding a bus and cheerfully asking strangers if they had read the
Mormon gospel. ``We're here to offer people the truth.'' And the
number of people across the country, and around the world willing
to embrace that truth has been, in the view of many religious
scholars, nothing short of phenomenal. By Diego Ribadebeira.
</P>
