to the Republican bastion of South Carolina, the South is serving
up some of the most competitive Senate contests in the country in
the 1998 mid-term elections. The parties are vying for open seats
in Arkansas and Kentucky and struggling to defend incumbents in
North Carolina (Republican Sen. Lauch Faircloth) and South Carolina
(Democrat Ernest Hollings). Relatively strong Democratic turnout in
the Georgia primary could also make things interesting for Sen.
Paul Coverdell (R-Ga.) in the peach state. (Foskett, Cox News
Service)
