   BOMBING-CLINTON-TV (Undated) Packaging sells. But if television
is just radio with pictures, the words must still be important,
right? President Clinton and his wordsmiths obviously think so. In
Monday's unprecedented mea culpa to the masses, the president spoke
for about four minutes and used the words ``me,'' ``my,''
``myself'' and ``I'' 46 times _ about once every five seconds.
Yesterday, over a span of eight minutes, only 15 such personal
references, but 52 uses of the all-inclusive ``we'' and ``our.''
