nation's transmission system _ the towers and high-voltage lines
that carry power from generation plants to utilities and,
increasingly, between sellers and buyers in the fledgling wholesale
power market. Regulators now require utilities that own sections of
the transmission grid to transport power produced by any source,
even competitors. By Michael Parrish.
