<P>
   &UR; THE SONGWRITER SAID IT BEST &LR;
</P>
<P>
   From  &UR; Bob Dylan &LR; 's ``It's Alright Ma, I'm Only Bleeding,''
remembered by  &UR; Dan &LR;   &UR; Mankin &LR; : ``While preachers preach of evil
fates/ Teachers teach that knowledge waits/ Can lead to
hundred-dollar plates/ Goodness hides behind its gates/ But even
the president of the United States/ Sometimes must have/ To stand
naked.''
</P>
<P>
   P.S. A Washington Post staff member injured in an auto accident
this week was asked several questions by a paramedic who came to
the rescue: ``What is your name? Who is the president? Who is the
president's girlfriend?''
</P>
<P>
   Washington Fire Department Battalion Chief  &UR; Alvin Carter &LR;  told
the newspaper, ``It's only because so much attention has been paid
throughout the world to the president's situation. It was an
attempt to make the situation a little more light.''
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
