<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Braves on deck: San Diego Padres
 &HT;    By Thomas Stinson
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   _ When: 7:40 p.m.
</P>
<P>
   _ Where: Turner Field.
</P>
<P>
   _ TV: TBS.
</P>
<P>
   _ Probable starting pitchers: RHP John Smoltz (11-2, 3.32; 11-7,
2.90 lifetime vs. Padres) vs. RHP Joey Hamilton (10-10, 4.58; 2-7,
5.49 lifetime vs. Braves).
</P>
<P>
   _ Notes: Hamilton is having a 4-1 second half, and one of the
highlights was his Aug. 11 victory against the Braves. Against a
club he has had trouble handling during his young career, he went
seven innings and gave up six hits and one run. Hamilton survived a
six-game losing streak that lasted through May into June and has
been 7-3 since June 8. His 4.58 ERA, higher than the 3.70 career
rate he opened the season with, has been hurt by the big game. He
has given up five or more earned runs nine times, but in 13 other
starts he gave up two earned runs or less. His hits-to-innings
ratio is high (172 hits in 169 innings), and his 77 walks are
fifth-most in the league. Smoltz, the medical marvel, has gone 7-1
since coming off his second stay on the DL on June 20 and is riding
a six-game winning streak in his last eight starts. He has beaten
the Padres and Hamilton once this year (6-3 on May 7), when he gave
up two runs in the first inning but then drove in three runs with a
double and a single.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
