<SLUG> BC-BUSINESS-LADN </SLUG>
  
<TEXT>
<P>
   Here are the business news stories the Los Angeles Daily News
plans to move for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs
of Friday, Aug. 21, and thereafter. The stories will carry the
``f'' financial news category code unless otherwise noted. For
questions about stories, contact Tom Hicks at the Daily News, (818)
713-3702.
</P>
<P>
   INCOMNET-FINANCES (Los Angeles) _ Two days after reporting heavy
quarterly losses, long-distance telecommunications marketer
Incomnet Inc. said Thursday it is in talks with its main lender,
shareholder and supplier to restructure finances. By Ben Sullivan.
</P>
<P>
   DISNEY-BIRNBAUM (Los Angeles) _ The Walt Disney Co. signs a
distribution deal with high-profile producer Roger Birnbaum for up
to five movies a year through 2003. Birnbaum's newly formed
Spyglass Entertainment will finance the projects. By Dave McNary.
</P>
<P>
   ELECTRIC-SCHWINN (Los Angeles) _ Thrusting bicycle maker Schwinn
into the electric-bicycle market, L.A.-based Currie Technologies
Inc. has licensed its new propulsion module technology to the
Boulder, Colo.-based giant. By Enrique Rivero.
</P>
