   ``There has been a very dirty, very nasty little war on
terrorism ongoing for some time, but it is clear it has
escalated,'' Goss said. ``We are having a war and people need to be
behind it and support the president.''
</P>
<P>
   ``This could be a long campaign -- six months, two years, three
years -- and there will be casualties,'' Gingrich said.
</P>
<P>
   Goss said public officials must stress the ``nature of
ugliness'' of terrorists.
</P>
<P>
   ``They don't care about suicide. They don't care about the
