Park in Long Island City. No one can say that New York is outdoor
sculpture-challenged. If you travel around the city in summer, in
addition to the time-honored monuments that appear at every turn,
you will find many a new work or works ensconced on temporarily
sites. (J. Emilio Flores/New York Times Photo)
</P>
