-- Jeanine Tesori drew on eclectic instruments, played by six
musicians, for her incidental music and songs accompanying
Shakespeare's ``Twelfth Night'' at the Vivian Beaumont. ``I
surround myself with people who believe in the theater the way it
was: that is, if you tell a great story, audiences will come, and
if you make music that comes out of your heart, people will
listen,'' she says. (Nancy Siesel/New York Times Photo)
