<P>
   (NYT1) LENOX, Mass. -- Aug. 20, 1998 -- ADV. FOR SUN., AUG. 23
-- TANGLEWOOD-FESTIVAL-1, 8-20 -- Seiji Ozawa, the longtime music
director of the Boston Symphony, at the Serge Koussevitzky Music
Shed at Tanglewood. Veterans of past summers at Tanglewood attest
that with Ozawa, who studied at the center in 1960, more closely
involved in its activities than ever before, this has been one of
the most rewarding festival seasons in recent memory. (Alan E.
Solomon/New York Times Photo) *LITE
