8-20 -- Tatiana Benharbone follows her dog, Ms. Kitty, into her
cab. Ms. Benharbone is one of the few Holocaust survivors still
actively working in the Boston area, a reminder of an era fast
fading from public memory. ``There's this terrible hole inside
you,'' she says. ``Acton isn't home. I don't think anyplace is
home.'' (Suzanne Kreiter/Boston Globe Photo)
